== Playing style and equipment==
{{POV-section|date=April 2009}}
Monfils is usually described as a baseliner who uses placement and consistency to beat his opponents. Monfils is well known for his athleticism and his court coverage, regularly using slide to retrieve balls.<ref>{{cite web|title="I'm more of an artist"|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/sports/tennis/news/story?id=5376000|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=8 October 2012|author=Carmen Renee Thompson|date=July 13, 2010}}</ref>  His ability to go from defense to offense quickly can take his opponents by surprise. Monfils occasionally demonstrates that he is capable of generating significant pace on his groundstrokes. He has a reputation for showmanship and high-risk shotmaking.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gael Monfils and Losing in Style|url=http://www.newyorker.com/online/blogs/sportingscene/2011/09/gale-monfils-and-losing-in-style.html|accessdate=8 October 2012|newspaper=The New Yorker|date=September 2, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Tsonga Beats Monfils 7-5, 6-3|url=http://www.guardiannewsngr.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=73143:-tsonga-beats-monfils-7-5-6-3&catid=58:abroad&Itemid=623|accessdate=8 October 2012|newspaper=The Guardian|date=8 January 2012}}</ref>   During his own service games, he tends to go for an ace or a one-two combination to finish off the points early.He is also known for dancing to celebrate victories.He uses a semi-western grip forehand and a combination of continental/semi-western on his backhand.
Monfils possesses a strong serve capable of reaching over 140&nbsp;mph but his main focus is consistency and placement rather than power. Monfils was sponsored by Nike for clothes and shoes but changed to [[K-Swiss]] in 2010 and was sponsored by [[Head (company)|Head]] for racquets but changed to [[Prince Sports|Prince]] in 2009. His current racquet of choice is the Prince EXO3 Rebel 95. His current string of choice is the Luxilon Big Banger ALU Power 16L String.
<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/tennis/4388814.stm|work=BBC News |title=Monfils tames Grosjean in Lyon|date=29 October 2005|accessdate=3 May 2010}}</ref>
<ref>[http://www.nysun.com/sports/peculiar-evolution-of-todays-tennis-serve/57251/ The Peculiar Evolution of Today's Tennis Serve <U+2013> 25 June 2007 <U+2013> The New York Sun<!--Bot generated title-->]</ref>

==Personal life==
Ga<U+00EB>l is nicknamed "''La Monf''", or occasionally "''Sliderman''" due to his unusual sliding technique, especially on [[clay]] surfaces.<ref name=connexion>{{cite web|title=Profile: Ga<U+00EB>l Monf The next Noah?|url=http://www.connexionfrance.com/Profile-Gael-Monfils-11675-news-article.html|publisher=The Connexion|accessdate=8 October 2012|date=May 2012}}</ref>  He is of Caribbean heritage: his father, Rufin, a former football player employed as an agent for France Telecom, comes from the island of [[Guadeloupe]]. His mother, Sylvette, comes from the nearby island of [[Martinique]] and is a nurse. He has a younger brother, [[Daryl Monfils|Daryl]], who plays tennis.  Gael and Daryl played doubles together in the [[2012 Open Sud de France <U+2013> Doubles|2012 Open Sud de France]], losing in the first round.

Monfils considers [[Arthur Ashe]] to be his favorite player. He is fond of listening to music, particularly R&B. If he did not play tennis, he would play basketball. He is a huge fan of the NBA's [[Denver Nuggets]] and his favorite basketball player is [[Carmelo Anthony]].<ref name=connexion/> His best friends are countrymen and former juniors [[Josselin Ouanna]] and [[Paterne Mamata]] and fellow pros [[Richard Gasquet]], [[Gilles Simon]], [[Jo-Wilfried Tsonga]]. Monfils is also a fan of football and his two favorite football clubs are [[Arsenal F.C.]] and [[Paris-Saint Germain]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Monfils stretches the boundaries|url=http://www.smh.com.au/articles/2007/01/18/1169095907209.html?page=1|accessdate=8 October 2012|newspaper=Sydney Morning Herald|date=January 19, 2007}}</ref> 

He was coached by countryman and former ATP pro [[Thierry Champion]] (since September 2004) but they parted company in September 2006. Nevertheless, Monfils's fitness trainer is still R<U+00E9>mi Barbarin. Monfils announced a partnership with a new coach, [[Tarik Benhabiles]], in May 2007. However, for the 2008 season, Monfils has hired [[Roger Rasheed]] as his coach.  In 2011, Monfils parted ways with Rasheed and announced that his fitness coach, Patrick Chamagne would take the reins as his new fulltime coach.

Monfils appeared in the music video for "Hello" by Martin Solveig and Dragonette.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hello - Martin Solveig,Dragonette Single Review|url=http://www.allgigs.co.uk/view/review/5407/Martin_Solveig_Dragonette_Hello_Single_Review.html|publisher=AllGigs|accessdate=8 October 2012}}</ref> 

Monfils was considered an athletics prodigy at school and won the French under-13 and under-14 100m championships. It was only his love for tennis that stopped him going on to compete at a higher level. His coach is on record as saying that Monfils could have made the Olympic 100m final such was his talent.

